group-guess (1.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium
  * This adds a proper manpage, which I'll have to see if it includes
    automatically.
  * This fixes a long-standing bug where the cover images had an object
    slightly longer than SVG canvase size, causing the bottom to get cut off.
  * This fixes an underwater Unicode handling bug by changing answer
    comparison from x.lower().strip() to x.casefold().strip(), which should
    catch some non-matching sequences for comparison.

 -- LandonTheCoder <100165458+LandonTheCoder@users.noreply.github.com>  Tue, 10 May 2022 15:36:48 -0400

group-guess (1.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium
  * This is the public version containing the fixes of 1.2.0-2 and 1.2.0-3.
    Those fixes include:
  * Add tracking of example files in debian/group-guess.examples
  * Add tracking of documentation files README.md and SAVE-FORMAT.md in
    debian/docs
  * Support varied verbosity levels. This is implemented by a new option to
    the debug logger, and the user can specify --verbose 1 or more times to
    override an input file.
  * Clean out a few unnecessary example files in the debian/ directory.

